Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "slažete" in different forms and positions:

1. Da li se slažete sa mnom? (*slažete*, present tense) (Do you agree with me?)
2. Ja sam se slagao sa tom odlukom. (*slagao*, past tense) (I agreed with that decision.)
3. Oni su se složili da će doći na sastanak. (*složili*, past tense) (They agreed to come to the meeting.)
4. Slažem se sa tobom u potpunosti. (*slažem se*, present tense) (I completely agree with you.)
5. Kada bi se vi složili sa mnom, sve bi bilo lakše. (*složili*, past tense) (If you agreed with me, everything would be easier.)
6. Da li bi se složili sa tim da se sastanak održi u petak? (*složili*, past tense) (Would you agree that the meeting should be held on Friday?)
7. Molim vas da se slažete sa ovim predlogom. (*slažete*, present tense) (I ask you to agree with this proposal.)
8. Ako se ne složimo, nećemo moći da postignemo dogovor. (*složimo*, future tense) (If we don't agree, we won't be able to reach an agreement.)
9. Ne slažeš se sa mnom, ali to nije važno. (*slažeš se*, present tense) (You don't agree with me, but it's not important.)
10. Da li se ti slažeš sa tim da bismo trebali preduzeti nešto? (*slažeš*, present tense) (Do you agree that we should take action?)

I hope these examples help!